<div class="gallery fadeGallery">
  <h2> Storage </h2>

  <br>
  
  <p>
    
    Storage is also a very important part of your pc. The HDD or SSD is where you store files such as your OS, for example; Windows, Linux, and MacOS HDD or Hard Disk Drive is for storing your files. Every drive has their own speeds, the most common speeds for HDD is 5400 RPM (Rotations Per Minute) and 7200 RPM the faster the drive can spin, the faster you can access your files.</p>
    <br> 
    <p>  Currently the fastest HDD speed is 15,000RPM, although it spins amazingly fast, it is much slower compared to SSDs. Speaking of which, an SSD or Solid State Drive is made out of flash memory which is much faster than any HDD. Since it is using flash memory, it can only read and write so many times before it dies. The price of SSDs are also much higher than normal HDDs, as a normal 1TB HDD costs about $40-70 depending on the brand, while a 1TB SSD can cost upwards towards $350. 

  </p>
</div>

